data.name: Pork Fried Rice Delight
data.quickTastyDescription: A quick and savory stir-fried rice dish with tender pork and vibrant vegetables, perfect for a satisfying meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat sesame oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add diced pork and cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes.
Push pork to the side and add minced garlic. Saut√© for 30 seconds until fragrant.
Add frozen mixed vegetables and cook until heated through, about 2-3 minutes.
Push everything to the side and pour beaten eggs into the skillet. Scramble until fully cooked.
Stir in the cooked rice and soy sauce, mixing everything together. Heat through for another 3-5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste, and garnish with chopped green onions before serving.
